# VirtualPostMail (TruResidence) Analysis

## Plan
- [x] Open https://www.virtualpostmail.com/truresidence/
- [x] Capture Hero section (headline, subheadline, CTAs)
- [x] Capture Pricing and Tier information
- [x] Capture Trust signals (testimonials, stats, etc.)
- [x] Capture Comparison tables (if any)
- [x] Capture Key messaging and USPs
- [x] Capture FAQ topics
- [x] Note Design style (colors, layout, fonts)
- [x] Update scratchpad with findings

## Initial Findings (Hero & Messaging)
- **Hero Headline**: "Get a remote U.S. residential address"
- **Hero Subheadline**: "TruResidence provides you with a verified U.S. residential address, helping you maintain U.S. ties for personal accounts and receive mail online. Anytime. Anywhere."
- **CTA**: "Get TruResidence" (and "Get Started" in header)
- **Key Messaging**: 
    - "Lease agreement add-on": Rent a space by signing a lease agreement to confirm occupancy.
    - "Utility bill for additional proof": Option to set up utility service for a bill in your name.
    - "Security of mail data": Secure storage in access-controlled facilities.
    - "Accepted for banking, credit, IDs": Targets personal accounts primarily.

## Detailed Findings
- **Pricing**:
    - TruRes Essentials: $300/mo (billed monthly)
    - TruRes Extended: $400/mo (billed monthly)
    - TruRes Extended+: $250/mo (billed annually)
    - **Lease Add-on**: $400 processing fee + Monthly base rent (varies) + $1200 security deposit.
    - **Utility Add-on**: Requires minimum 2-month lease.
- **Trust Signals**: No specific client testimonials found on TruResidence page, but VPM has broader trust signals (Trustpilot link in footer usually).
- **Comparison Table**: Compares TruResidence vs. Traditional Renting vs. Friend/Family address. Highlights "No credit requirements", "No SSN required" for TruResidence compared to traditional renting.
- **USPs**: Real residential address (not CMRA), utility bill in name, lease agreement.
- **FAQ/Restrictions**: 
    - No Google Business Profile support.
    - No business formation documents (they recommend Virtual Mailbox for that). This is a big weak point for founders needing LLCs.
    - Mail delay: ~1 week (picked up weekly).
    - No unique suite number (shared like a household).
- **Design Style**: 
    - **Colors**: White, light blue, dark blue (#004c97 primary), green accents.
    - **Layout**: Clean, sectioned, use of custom illustrations and icons.
    - **Fonts**: Modern sans-serif (Inter or similar).
